ZH: 今天我打算早点关门大吉，好好休息一下。
EN: Today I plan to close early and have a good rest.

ZH: 请记得在离开前关门大吉。
EN: Please remember to close the door when you leave.

ZH: 关门大吉，不要让别人进来。
EN: Close the door and don't let anyone in.

ZH: 你可以走了，别忘了说一声“关门大吉”。
EN: You can go now, don't forget to say "close the door".

ZH: 我在外面等着你，你进来了就要记得“关门大吉”。
EN: I'm waiting for you outside, remember to "close the door" when you come in.

ZH: 下班的时候别忘了说一声“关门大吉”。
EN: Don't forget to say "close the door" when you finish work.

ZH: 明天是周末，开心工作，关门大吉。
EN: Tomorrow is the weekend, work happily and close the door.

ZH: 在你走之前，请关门大吉。
EN: Please close the door before you leave.

ZH: 办公室要关门了，关门大吉。
EN: The office is closing, close the door.

ZH: 下班时间到了，大家一起说一声“关门大吉”吧。
EN: It's time to finish work, let's all say "close the door".

ZH: 今晚我早点回家，关门大吉。
EN: I'm going to go home early tonight, close the door.

ZH: 请保持门口整洁并确保关门大吉。
EN: Please keep the entrance clean and make sure to close the door.

ZH: 请不要在办公室里大声喧哗，关门大吉。
EN: Please don't make loud noises in the office, close the door.

ZH: 明天我会提前关门大吉，准时到家。
EN: Tomorrow I will close the door early and be home on time.

ZH: 开会前请先把门关好，关门大吉。
EN: Please close the door before the meeting, close the door.

ZH: 不要让门一直敞开，记得说一声“关门大吉”。
EN: Don't leave the door open, remember to say "close the door".

ZH: 如果你不记得关门大吉，我可以提醒你。
EN: If you forget to close the door, I can remind you.

ZH: 请在工作结束后立即关闭门，关门大吉。
EN: Please close the door immediately after work, close the door.

ZH: 我们离开前一定要记得说一声“关门大吉”。
EN: We must remember to say "close the door" before we leave.
